<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="563" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,342,691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,522,547]" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Forewing length is 
<quantity box="[561,687,523,547]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14 mm</quantity>
in males and 13.5 mm in females. Externally, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daniel" authorityYear="1954" box="[1244,1352,523,547]" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lactuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[1244,1352,523,547]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">L. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs clearly from its congeners by its long and broad longitudinal strip and significantly reduced forewing pattern elements. Differences of the male and female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daniel" authorityYear="1954" box="[818,925,595,619]" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lactuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis box="[818,925,595,619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">L. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from those of its closest relative 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Višinskas, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Višinskas" authorityYear="2018" box="[1312,1393,595,618]" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lactuca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="563" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="witti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1312,1393,595,618]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">L. witti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="563">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="2" pageNumber="563" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are described in the diagnosis of the latter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
